extraQCShopRule: <color=#ffab6e>Purchase Certificates</color> can be obtained from Supplies stages and Missions. They can be used to exchange for items in the <color=#ec3140>Purchase Certificates Store</color>.

In the <color=#ec3140>Purchase Certificates Store</color>, <color=#ffab6e>Module Data Blocks</color> will display an <color=#ec3140>exchange countdown timer</color> 30 days before it is restocked. 
- The exchange count for <color=#ffab6e>Module Data Blocks</color> will be reset at the start of every month. After the exchange limit for the current month is reached, 
it will change to the 'awaiting restock' status.
- Whether or not it is in the awaiting restock status, the exchange count for <color=#ffab6e>Module Data Blocks</color> will reset after the countdown timer ends.

<color=#ffab6e>Note: </color>In the <color=#ec3140>Purchase Certificates Store</color>, <color=#ffab6e>Tokens</color> will also display an <color=#ec3140>exchange countdown timer</color> 30 days before they are restocked. 
After the countdown timer ends, regardless of the current exchange status of the <color=#ffab6e>Tokens</color>, the <color=#ffab6e>Tokens</color> will be 
swapped for a new batch of <color=#ffab6e>Tokens</color>.
repQCShopRule: · Certain event rewards that cannot be obtained again will be converted into <color=#a67dff>Intelligence Certificates</color> based on the corresponding ratio. The <color=#a67dff>Intelligence Certificates</color> conversion ratio can be checked in the <color=#a67dff>Intelligence Certificate Conversion Rules</color> in the corresponding event.
· Items in the <color=#a67dff>Intelligence Certification Area</color> will have the available purchase amount increased on top of the existing amount and have new items added when event reruns begin.
